    QUESTION THE EXPERTS: PDF Only

    A number of my patients who were successfully treated with alprazolam for panic disorder have had trouble discontinuing their medication, even with slow tapering. They could get down to between 0.5 and 2.0 mg and would then show withdrawal symptoms—easily startled“ tachycardia, photophobia, night sweats, and increased nighttime anxiety and nightmares. These were not symptoms that were characteristic of their prediscontinuation anxiety. What can be helpful?

    SHADER, RICHARD I. MD

    Author Information
    Journal of Clinical Psychopharmacology 7(3):p 208, June 1987.
